Mark Roenigk - Career Profile

















Mark Roenigk






 


 




mark w.
roenigk
                                                                                      Page Two







Career Profile
Areas of Expertise
Experience
Publications/Recognition
Education

                                                      
  


EXECUTIVE CAREER PROFILE



Cloud Computing / Data Center Infrastructure / Operations / Supply Chain  

A proven, engaged, and results oriented leader with a passion for leading transformational change and driving business results.  Significant international experience in highly technical and complex business environments.  Breadth and depth of experience has led to many innovative approaches to managing business operations and the ability to create agile supply chain operations to meet ever changing business requirements.  Successful track record in providing strategic leadership in new product development & introduction, Cloud computing, data center infrastructure, supply chain optimization, operations management, quality assurance, employee development, and customer care across a variety of industries and business channels.  Team oriented and collaborative partner skilled in all facets of business from daily operational execution and partnership with the business leaders to develop new products, services, businesses, and sales channels.  
 

 

INTRODUCTION
  
Mark is a engaging leader with significant international business experience and a warm leadership style.  His collaborative approach and team orientation have been a big part of his success and effectiveness in building high performing organizations.   Mark is a strong believer in the application of process excellence & six sigma methodologies to build a strong operational foundation for sustained success.   Mark has both breadth and depth of subject matter expertise enabling his team to quickly deliver operational results while developing long term strategies for success.    He brings a very disciplined approach to operations and the metrics associated wtih measuring operational performance.  

 
EXPERIENCE
  
Mark spent most of his career in the high tech industry working for leading companies such as eBay, XM Satellite Radio, Intuit, Microsoft, and Compaq/HP.  He has significant experience in high volume and complex product launches in hardware, software, internet and services.   Mark is currently COO at Rackspace, the Open Cloud Computing leader.    Previously, Mark was Chief Procurement Officer and VP of Operational Excellence at eBay/PayPal.    In 2006 he was named Senior Vice President of Operations for XM Satellite Radio responsible for a variety of operational functions.   Prior to that Mark spent over 14 years in the PC Software industry working for industry leading companies such as Intuit, Microsoft and Compaq/HP.     


LEADERSHIP

Mark's ability to teach, coach, and mentor is what differentiates him from most other executives.  He has the reputation for building strong, cohesive, high-performing teams.   He has the unique ability to transfer knowledge to others and quickly ramp the caliber and performance of an organization.   He is a collaborative change agent that has consistently delivered exceptional results for the organization and the company.  His organizations consistently rank in the upper tier in employee and customer satisfaction.   Mark has been recognized for excellence in leadership at Microsoft, Intuit, and Clarke American.                                


