Rackspace Confirms Departure of COO Roenigk









Tony Owusu




Jun 1, 2017 11:16 AM EDT













 


























































 Web hosting company Rackspace  (RAX) confirmed the departure of COO Mark Roenigk, according to the San Antonio Business Journal on Thursday, after nearly 8 years at that position with the company. He will be leaving the company June 28.  David Meredith, a senior vice president at Century Link  (CTL) , will take over for Roenigk. "Rackspace is strongly positioned to succeed in a market where businesses want help moving out of their legacy data centers so they can be more strategic in their IT operations," Meredith said in a statement.  Comcast  (CMCSA)  and Alphabet  (GOOGL) are just some of the tech names in Jim Cramer's Action Alerts PLUS portfolio. Get his insights on the biggest names in tech here. 



 



 










































